00:01:49.790 --> 00:01:53.320
And thinking about that role,
the role that culture has

00:01:53.320 --> 00:01:59.540
in this conversation and literature
in particular, I'd like to go back

00:01:59.540 --> 00:02:07.240 position:56%
to 1947 when Rogers and Hammerstein
premiered South Pacific on Broadway,

00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:11.940
based on the book "Tales of the
South Pacific" by James Michener.

00:02:11.940 --> 00:02:16.960
The song that stirred
quite a controversy was

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:19.590 position:56%
"You've got to be carefully taught".

00:02:19.590 --> 00:02:22.980
And here quickly is a first stanza.

00:02:22.980 --> 00:02:25.910
You've got to be taught
to hate and fear.

00:02:25.910 --> 00:02:29.200
You've got to be taught
from year to year.

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:32.990
It's got to be drummed
in your dear little ear.

00:02:32.990 --> 00:02:35.860
You've got to be carefully taught.

00:02:35.860 --> 00:02:39.370
Many letters and the papers of
Oscar Hammerstein at the Library

00:02:39.370 --> 00:02:44.560
of Congress demonstrated the
polarizing nature of this tune,

00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:48.970
very much meant by both Rogers
and Hammerstein to be a comment

00:02:48.970 --> 00:02:51.750
on the racial prejudice
of the times.

00:02:51.750 --> 00:02:57.150
And by the way the library has the
piano vocal scores of South Pacific

00:02:57.150 --> 00:03:00.760
in the performing arts reading
room and the sound recording

00:03:00.760 --> 00:03:05.930 position:56%
of the original Broadway cast in
the recorded sound reference center.

00:03:05.930 --> 00:03:11.640
But our conversation today takes a
very different and optimistic turn.

00:03:11.640 --> 00:03:15.980
Our premise does include the
value of language and education,

00:03:15.980 --> 00:03:20.870
but from a different place, by
sharing values, culture and stories

00:03:20.870 --> 00:03:24.190
from the heritage, their
heritage our authors

00:03:24.190 --> 00:03:27.500
and illustrator make
positive contributions

00:03:27.500 --> 00:03:29.600
to the future of our children.

00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:32.650
