00:08:11.860 --> 00:08:17.600
As ground work some statistics from
the migration policy institute here

00:08:17.600 --> 00:08:21.100
in Washington D.C. that
you might find interesting.

00:08:21.100 --> 00:08:25.050
As of 2016 the US foreign
born population

00:08:25.050 --> 00:08:30.000
and the US foreign children
accounted for 81 million people.

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:33.160
More than a quarter
of our population.

00:08:33.160 --> 00:08:38.600
In 2014, 1.3 million
people migrated to the US,

00:08:38.600 --> 00:08:42.440
a figure that includes
estimates of the undocumented.

00:08:42.440 --> 00:08:49.580
The top countries of origin in
order were India, China, Mexico.

00:08:49.580 --> 00:08:51.090
Canada and the Philippines.

00:08:51.090 --> 00:08:54.910
And for those of you
who work with children

00:08:54.910 --> 00:08:57.410
and families you might
be interested to know

00:08:57.410 --> 00:09:01.500
that in 2014 17.5 million
children lived

00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:05.680
with at least one parent
who was an immigrant.

00:09:05.680 --> 00:09:11.900
And interestingly 88% of children
of immigrant parents are born

00:09:11.900 --> 00:09:13.570
in the United States

00:09:13.570 --> 00:09:17.180
and are therefore second
generation Americans.

00:09:17.180 --> 00:09:21.020
All of those figures
represent a quadruple growth

00:09:21.020 --> 00:09:27.030
in the immigrants present
in the US since 1970.

00:09:27.030 --> 00:09:28.950
So yes, we are a nation
of immigrants

00:09:28.950 --> 00:09:33.000
and our collective identity is
based on the Statue of Liberty.

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:38.230
Given your poor, your tired masses
and all the rest of that inscribed

00:09:38.230 --> 00:09:42.010
at the base of the Statue of
Liberty, but as we know especially

00:09:42.010 --> 00:09:47.040
in this election year there
is considerable backlash

00:09:47.040 --> 00:09:49.920
against the foreign
born in our country.

00:09:49.920 --> 00:09:54.150
This native rhetoric is nothing
new sadly; it's what Dr. Alan Krout

00:09:54.150 --> 00:10:02.180
of American University refers
to as old wine in new bottles.

00:10:02.180 --> 00:10:03.660
Our nation unfortunately
has a history

00:10:03.660 --> 00:10:08.900
of native sentiments particularly
in times of economic downturn.

00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:11.810
Throughout history we've selected
different groups to target

00:10:11.810 --> 00:10:14.960
with suspicions of their
religion, with accusations

00:10:14.960 --> 00:10:18.430
that they bring disease or
lawlessness, that they are a threat

00:10:18.430 --> 00:10:21.930
to civil order or our
national security.

00:10:21.930 --> 00:10:26.690
So think of anti-Catholicism,
which regard to Irish and Germans

00:10:26.690 --> 00:10:29.370
in the early 20th century
and the backlash

00:10:29.370 --> 00:10:32.040
against Muslim Americans today.

00:10:32.040 --> 00:10:36.560
Think of quota systems to limit
the foreign born, and legislations

00:10:36.560 --> 00:10:39.650
like the Chinese Exclusion
Act of the 1800's.

00:10:39.650 --> 00:10:44.710
Think of internment camps for
Japanese Americans in World War II,

00:10:44.710 --> 00:10:50.200
and think today of these
conversations about sparkling walls

00:10:50.200 --> 00:10:53.740
that we will build at our borders.

00:10:53.740 --> 00:10:56.940
And yet, we are all
here, all Americans,

00:10:56.940 --> 00:11:02.580 position:56%
all trying to find a way forward and
a way to love families and children.

00:11:02.580 --> 00:11:06.820
And in this effort we turn as a
people, as we always have I think

00:11:06.820 --> 00:11:11.030
to the arts, to help us name the
experience and to build bridges.

