that affirm kids and especially

00:59:25.930 --> 00:59:30.120
when they are in elementary
school, I think with middle school,

00:59:30.120 --> 00:59:32.240
high school is a different thing

00:59:32.240 --> 00:59:34.820
because we can have
more deep conversations

00:59:34.820 --> 00:59:37.800
about races, inequality, injustice.

00:59:37.800 --> 00:59:40.610
And I do go there with
elementary kids,

00:59:40.610 --> 00:59:44.690
it's not that I'm avoiding the
topic, but I am trying to look

00:59:44.690 --> 00:59:48.770
for those other books that
you know create a sense

00:59:48.770 --> 00:59:51.380
of empowerment of kids and hope.

00:59:51.380 --> 00:59:54.570 position:56%
So I'm curious to hear your thoughts
and if you have struggled with that

00:59:54.570 --> 00:59:57.240
when you choose your
topics for your stories

00:59:57.240 --> 01:00:02.000
and what's your reaction to that?

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:03.590
&gt;&gt; Rene Colato Lainez: Yeah
for me it's to be authentic.

01:00:03.590 --> 01:00:09.840 position:56%
When I am writing a story I focus on
the positive in the authentic way.

01:00:09.840 --> 01:00:12.860
Because if I want to talk about
Mexican I don't have to talk

01:00:12.860 --> 01:00:17.530
about their sombreros or
singing and eating tacos.

01:00:17.530 --> 01:00:22.170
There are many wonderful
things to talk about Mexico.

01:00:22.170 --> 01:00:26.350
And also in my country El
Salvador, so I go for the positive.

01:00:26.350 --> 01:00:31.580 position:56%
I see that the positive and the
authentic is the most powerful thing

01:00:31.580 --> 01:00:39.520
to talk about for children to
love their culture and language.

01:00:39.520 --> 01:00:42.640
&gt;&gt; Meg Medina: And also where
you're picking the books.

01:00:42.640 --> 01:00:50.450
So you know Los Americas award
winners, [Inaudible] Asian Pacific,

01:00:50.450 --> 01:00:54.440
literature winners, I think
you want the best examples

01:00:54.440 --> 01:00:55.950
because when books are selected

01:00:55.950 --> 01:00:59.820
for those lists sometimes I
think those questions come up.

01:00:59.820 --> 01:01:03.790
Does this book authentically
portray the experience

01:01:03.790 --> 01:01:06.250
but also respectfully
portray the experience?

01:01:06.250 --> 01:01:13.150 position:56%
I write about folks often families
who are from moderate to low income,

01:01:13.150 --> 01:01:18.130 position:56%
but I think respectfully and in a
way that doesn't show them as broken

01:01:18.130 --> 01:01:20.880
or excessive suffering and so on.

01:01:20.880 --> 01:01:22.920
I think it's developing a pallet

01:01:22.920 --> 01:01:24.900
for where you're searching
for those books.

01:01:24.900 --> 01:01:28.950 position:56%
And I'm always encourage when people
are looking for them and I ask you

01:01:28.950 --> 01:01:32.050
to continue to ask your
librarians and your book sellers.

01:01:32.050 --> 01:01:36.260
Exert that sort of pressure; I
don't know if you feel that way.

01:01:36.260 --> 01:01:41.590
Your request of that material and
your conversation at that level

01:01:41.590 --> 01:01:45.250
with your local librarian
is important, it's essential

01:01:45.250 --> 01:01:48.450
because it raises their
awareness and cues them

01:01:48.450 --> 01:01:52.260
into the developing conversation.

01:01:52.260 --> 01:01:54.770
Because the conversation is
getting more interesting,

01:01:54.770 --> 01:01:57.960
it is getting more sophisticated.

01:01:57.960 --> 01:02:02.720
We are not just thankful
that anything is published.

01:02:02.720 --> 01:02:08.170
We're really holding things
to higher standards now.

01:02:08.170 --> 01:02:11.380
I was going to say I
think that's the --

01:02:11.380 --> 01:02:12.830
&gt;&gt; If there's one last question.

01:02:12.830 --> 01:02:19.760
&gt;&gt; I was waiting, which I don't
do very well, so this is good.

01:02:19.760 --> 01:02:23.700
A question and again more
of a comment and gratitude.

01:02:23.700 --> 01:02:28.790 position:56%
Having worked with a large
diversity population from homogenous

01:02:28.790 --> 01:02:32.250
to elite private school and
now I'm at a large urban school

01:02:32.250 --> 01:02:34.190
in Northern Virginia, probably
one of the most diverse

01:02:34.190 --> 01:02:36.310
in Northern Virginia
if not in the country

01:02:36.310 --> 01:02:39.550
and having a large
number of immigrants.

01:02:39.550 --> 01:02:42.470
Read aside and students not reading

01:02:42.470 --> 01:02:45.190
for pleasure is a whole other
panel we could spend several days

01:02:45.190 --> 01:02:46.490
discussing that.

01:02:46.490 --> 01:02:48.250
But getting books in their
hands that make sense.

01:02:48.250 --> 01:02:51.480
Students have lost the
ability to hear their own voice

01:02:51.480 --> 01:02:54.790 position:56%
